*i.n.s.o.</sup></td></tr>             <tr><td>sus2</td><td>sus2</td><td>2</=
td><td>5 <sup>*i.n.s.o.</sup></td></tr>             <tr><td>sus4</td><td>su=
s4</td><td>4</td><td>5 <sup>*i.n.s.o.</sup></td></tr>             <tr><td>d=
im</td><td>diminished</td><td>m3</td><td>b5</td></tr>             <tr><td>a=
ug</td><td>augmented</td><td>3</td><td>#5</td></tr>             </tbody></t=
able><p><sup>*i.n.s.o.</sup>) if not specified otherwise</p>               =
           <p>You may have noticed, that there are more combinations of 3rd=
s and 5ths. But in those cases the chords are usually reinterpreted, which =
means a different chord tone is taken as root.</p><table class=3D"qualityTa=
ble">             <tbody><tr><th>2</th><th>m3</th><th>3</th><th>4</th><th><=
